<seg id="850">Therefore, the Czech tax authorities should not have stated the electricity supplies in their ZM for 2005.</seg>
<seg id="851">The fact that both tax authorities treated the supply of electrical energy in their ZM as intra-Community supplies led to a difference of 503,881,939 CZK in MIAS.</seg>
<seg id="852">Final remark</seg>
<seg id="853">Through the cooperation, the goals of the BRH and the NK ä rke were achieved.</seg>
<seg id="854">Both auditors gained in-depth knowledge of the VAT administration systems in the Czech Republic and Germany.</seg>
<seg id="855">The cooperation revealed differences in the two systems and in the relevant legal provisions for VAT administration.</seg>
<seg id="856">During the parallel tests, interesting cases of intra-Community deliveries and acquisitions came to light.</seg>
<seg id="857">Some of them are worth further observation.</seg>
<seg id="858">On the basis of the audit results, both courts of auditors developed recommendations for the management of VAT.</seg>
<seg id="859">The follow-up of these recommendations in the form of a control review should be part of the further observation.</seg>
<seg id="860">The new experience and knowledge gained through the cooperation of the two courts of auditors is the basis for the successful implementation of future audits in the field of VAT administration.</seg>
<seg id="861">Communiqueness</seg>
<seg id="862">This report was written in Czech, English and German and signed by the President of the Supreme Control Office of the Czech Republic and the President of the Federal Audit Office of the Federal Republic of Germany.</seg>
