<seg id="72">According to the findings of the BRH, this requirement was largely implemented in Germany.</seg>
<seg id="73">During its audits, the NK found, particularly in the field of road construction, that the award of extensive services without lots or with only very large lots can affect competition and lead to a restriction to only a few large companies.</seg>
<seg id="74">Narrowing the market potential can lead to significant cost increases and carry the risk of price or other agreements.</seg>
<seg id="75">According to the provisions of both countries, under certain conditions, the contracting authorities can agree on additional or amended services with the companies already commissioned, which prove necessary after the conclusion of the original contract (No. 4.1).</seg>
