<seg id="673">Further calculations or investigations into the causes of this deviation were not documented.</seg>
<seg id="674">In a briefing, the contracting authority found no evidence of price dumping by the company commissioned.</seg>
<seg id="675">It remained unclear whether the estimated value was excessive or the offer price was too low.</seg>
<seg id="676">Later, the client rated the contracted company as a "cheap company" that could not meet quality or deadlines.</seg>
<seg id="677">In another tender, a construction service awarded the contract for an offer whose price was 35% higher than the value of the cost calculation.</seg>
<seg id="678">She did not cancel the call for tenders and cited the inappropriate justification that this company could be concluded to have an adequate calculation.</seg>
