<seg id="88">The Commission should support the Member States in this if desired.</seg>
<seg id="89">5. VAT testing at large companies</seg>
<seg id="90">The courts of auditors analysed the legal situation with regard to the VAT audit of large companies in both states.</seg>
<seg id="91">In addition, they used a questionnaire to collect information from the tax authorities that they considered important in this context.</seg>
<seg id="92">It became clear that the situation in both countries is different.</seg>
<seg id="93">The CZ has a system for selecting risky cases that includes a large amount of relevant data (including information on VAT audits, balance sheet data and profit and loss accounts).</seg>
<seg id="94">Overall, VAT control can be effectively controlled and analyzed.</seg>
<seg id="95">A special tax office for large companies is to be set up in 2012.</seg>
<seg id="96">There is no comparable system in Germany. This makes it difficult to manage and analyse VAT control as a whole.</seg>
<seg id="97">The German tax administration focuses more on the selection of relevant individual cases and relies in particular on data from the VAT pre-registrations or VAT declarations and the ZM.</seg>
<seg id="98">Various risk management components, which are to be improved, support the evaluation of this data.</seg>
<seg id="99">3. Examination procedure</seg>
<seg id="100">3.1 Examination procedures in the Czech Republic</seg>
<seg id="101">Department II - State Budget Revenue as well as the regional departments IX Pilsen, X eskk ä ufte Budjovice, XIII Brno and XV Ostrava examined in the period from May 2009 to February 2010.</seg>
<seg id="102">The audited bodies were the Czech Ministry of Finance and 25 F Ä: Tax Office (FA) Brno II, FA Brno III, FA Brno IV, FA in Br ü cken eclav, FA in Doma Lice, FA in Hodonic n, FA in Hradec Kr ü ckloe, FA in Cheb, FA in Jablonec nad Nisou, FA in Karlovy Vary, FA in Kralupy nad Vltavou, FA in Kraslice, FA Ostrava I, FA Ostrava III, FA in Pablonec nad Nisou, FA in Psek, FA in Prague, FA Pilsen, FA in Prague, FA 1, FA in Sokolok, FA in Prague, FA in Sokolok, FA in Molok and FA in Prague.</seg>
