<seg id="117">The two courts of auditors defined the following topics for their parallel audit: Evaluation of the recommendations given in the previous report; examination of selected cases of intra-Community transactions between taxpayers from the CZ and Germany, which could not be fully clarified during the first parallel audit; examination of selected intra-Community transactions classified as risky between taxpayers from the CZ and Germany; examination of the procedures of the two tax administrations with regard to intergovernmental administrative assistance in the recovery of VAT receivables; VAT audits of large companies.</seg>
